    <ImplicitInverseRef name="allLCsByOID" id="5c3adf5f-e911-4d77-ba4e-e5d9240396bb">
        <memberTypeInverse/>
        <type name="CMIF_LocationControllerByOidDt"/>
        <access>protected</access>
        <text>

##########################################
##########################################

We need to know what labour restrictions, location restrictions and sub block stacks are used for what location controllers.

SO this collection of CMIF_LocationControllerByOid has a string of the restriction, SBS or any other object oid and a reference
to the location controller.

When a restriction or SBS is deleted we have the OID but nothing else.
So instead of redrawing the whole terminal area we simply put the OID in the collection so that we know what location controllers to redraw.

This collection is also used is something is updated - resized etc.</text>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="allOIDSbyOIDString" id="a92ce1ff-b7db-4cd5-b6c4-bb6777d9f26c">
        <memberTypeInverse/>
        <type name="CMIF_LCsByOidDict"/>
        <access>protected</access>
        <text>##########################################
##########################################

We need to know what labour restrictions, location restrictions and sub block stacks are used for what location controllers.

SO this collection of CMIF_LocationControllersByOid has a string of the restriction, SBS or any other object oid and a reference
to all the location controllers.

When a restriction or SBS is deleted we have the OID but nothing else.
So instead of redrawing the whole terminal area we simply put the OID in the collection so that we know what location controllers to redraw.

This collection is also used if something is updated - resized etc.</text>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
